<b class="sectionheadertitle2">Voting Configuration</b>
<div class="infoModalOpenButton mainSection5">
    <i class="bi bi-book"></i>
    <div data-description class="hide">
        <h2>Voting Configuration</h2>
        <p>The device can be any machine that has Data Protection Tool Authenticator installed. Each device is connected to the Profile. Devices are distinguished by name and type (mobile, desktop, server, watch, etc.). Name is used to better recognize the device in question while the type is used in order to determine to which software the communication is established.</p>
        <p>Before registering a device unique token should be generated. This token is to be used as an access point for obtaining OAuth credentials which later can be used to communicate with the system.</p>
        <p>Profile requests a unique identifier for a device. Once the unique identifier is confirmed, the profile will create an OAuth application. The profile should obtain the access token and save it on the device. To distinguish device applications, the OAuth application name should be linked with the device name or unique id.</p>
    </div>
</div>
